Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Maxwell, out Lbw!! Needless review from Maxwell and he has to go. Pinpoint yorker from Archer and the Australian couldn't get his bat down on time. Pinned on the back pad and it rolled towards short fine leg. Umpire Nandan was quick to raise his finger and so was Maxwell to signal the T. That suggested that perhaps he might have got some bat on it but no, replays clearly show he hadn't and the rest is just a formality. Three Reds on HawkEye. It's started to rain as well!!!  Could well be the end of the innings. Maxwell lbw b Jofra Archer 5(5)

Commentary Text: Unadkat to Pant, out Caught by Stokes!! Vital, vital breakthrough! Might easily make a difference of about 10-15 runs to the eventual total. The deadly Pant has to depart but not before he has produced another thrill-a-minute epic. Backed away to make room for the big shot but one hand comes off in the process. Didn't get hold of it and skied this high towards long-on where Stokes moved to his left a fair bit to judge the skier perfectly. Two massive wickets in the over for RR, just the comeback they were looking for. Pant c Stokes b Unadkat 69(29) [4s-7 6s-5]

Commentary Text: D Kulkarni to Munro, out Caught by Buttler!! Huge strike and Rajasthan pocket Munro for a first-baller. That was full, swung in a bit and the batsman ended up playing down the wrong line. The inside edge was found and carried low to the keeper. Buttler went up and the umpire had no hesitation in giving it out. Munro on his part also did not want to review it as he knew he had edged it. The bowler did not appeal straightaway. He only went up after he saw the keeper appealing so confidently. Munro c Buttler b D Kulkarni 0(1)

Commentary Text: Boult to Gowtham, FOUR, It is a four, and it's been dropped in the deep by the captain, can you believe it! Crazy scenes here at the Kotla. This is going down to the last ball, it was on a fuller length and at the stumps, Gowtham flaunts his hitting prowess and hits the ball over long-on, timing wasn't great and Iyer at long-on spills it. Right through his hands there. Couldn't close the palms, the ball rips through it and bounces once before tagging the boundary ropes. Maxwell is around too, standing close-in and watching everything. Tries to slap the rebound off the ground into the playing area but fails to get a hand. Four! Six needed off the last ball!

Commentary Text: Boult to R Tripathi, out R Tripathi Run Out!! Boult calmly takes off the bails at the non striker's end and Tripathi will have to depart. This match is going Delhi's way now. Coming back to the ball, it was a perfect yorker outside off, Tripathi swings and misses; the ball goes to the keeper who balloons it to the bowler and he does the rest. Some headless running distilled in panic to be honest. Non-striker almost at the other end by the time Tripathi realizes that he has to run -- basically bullied into it -- and pays the price for it. R Tripathi run out (Pant/Boult) 9(8) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Mishra to Buttler, out Stumped!! Mishraji will be a popular man at the Kotla now. It was a terrific delivery from him, he brings his experience to the fore and drags his length back. Buttler, on the charge, was nowhere close to the pitch of this widish leg break and he misses it totally, running past it in his shimmy. He came in like thunder and went back like lighting. Buttler st Pant b Mishra 67(26) [4s-4 6s-7]
